HEADWORD: Yiddish
<hw>Yid"dish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>j⟦uum⟧disch</ets>, prop., Jewish, fr. <ets>Jude</ets> Jew. See
<er>Jew</er>, <er>Jewish</er>.]</ety> <def>A language used by German and
other Jews, being a Middle German dialect developed under Hebrew and
Slavic influence. It is written in Hebrew characters.</def>⟦br⟧
